                <note rend="inline" type="source">714.1515/628: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-04-24T12:00:00-06:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 24, 1928—noon</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received 4:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>52. Your telegram No. 33, April 19, 9 p.m.<note n="16" xml:id="d545fn16">See
                        footnote 14, <ref target="#pg_736">p. 736</ref>.</note> The Minister for
                    Foreign Affairs has just informed me that instructions were telegraphed this
                    morning to Coello to accept the proposal of Mr. Davis.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Mr. Davis and Guatemala.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Summerlin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
